Properties.Name: InstructionalText
Properties.Value: In some EU countries, authorities require reporting for exporting services to the other EU countries. This feature enables collecting EU service’s intertrade and its reporting to the authorities. Even this feature is primarily created for Belgian, French and Italian markets, it can be used in all EU countries if needed as reporting is configurable.

Properties.Value: Specifies whether the item charges have to be reported in the service declaration. If enabled, system checks the service transaction code for item charges and include them into service declarations.

Properties.Name: Tooltip
Properties.Value: Specifies which customer must be taken to compare his country code with the country code from the Company Information page. Only documents where these two codes are different will be considered for the service declaration. Bill-To.: The country code will be taken from the Bill-to Customer. Sell-To. : The country code will be taken from the Sell-to Customer.

Properties.Name: ToolTip
Properties.Value: Specifies which vendor must be taken to compare his country code with the country code from the Company Information page. Only documents where these two codes are different will be considered for the service declaration. Buy-From.: The country code will be taken from the Buy-From Vendor. Pay-To. : The country code will be taken from the Pay-To Vendor.
